        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>P<hi rend="sup">h</hi> Cabello</placeName> <date>5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> December 1852</date>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Isaac Leeser Esqre</addressee></p>
			<p><placeName>371 Walnut St. Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir&#33;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">A couple of months ago&#44; being in <placeName>Caracao</placeName>&#44; I was presented<lb/> with the accompanying prospectus&#44; by <persName>Samuel Piso&#44; Esqr</persName>&#44; of<lb/> <placeName>Barcelona</placeName>&#44; and wishing to become a subscriber to the &#8220;Occident<lb/> and American Jewish Advocate&#8221; &#40;Monthly Periodical&#41; I have<lb/> taken the liberty of filling up my name etc. in the said prospectus<lb/> and of addressing you on the subject. I am very wishful to be<lb/> in the possession of the 9 volumes&#44; which have already appeared<lb/> and the one which is now in progress of this periodical&#44; and you<lb/> will therefore extremely oblige me by handing the same to <persName>Captn.<lb/> Wilkins</persName> of the Barque Paez&#44; who will give you &#36;20.&#8212;that is<lb/> till the completion of the 10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> volume Ulto. <date>March 1853</date>&#44; and<lb/> also to let me know what two copies of the new translation of<lb/> the Holy Scriptures&#44; and one of the <sic>portuguese</sic> form of prayer<lb/> bound as noted in their respective subscriptions will amount<lb/> to&#44; so that I may be able to forward you a bill for the costs fur<lb/> &#8222;ther you oblige me by sending the same&#44; when ready to my ad<lb/> &#8222;dress&#44; and by the beginning of the 11<hi rend="sup">th</hi> volume of the monthly<lb/> to forward me the numbers as they are issued by the Dallett pack<lb/> &#8222;et&#44; for which I shall remit the subscription in due time.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Please be so kind as to inform me also&#44; what may be<lb/> the cost of a Hebrew grammar&#44; in English&#44; Lexicon&#44; and English<lb/> <hi rend="underline">&#38; Hebrew</hi></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>&#38; Hebrew&#44; and Hebrew &#38; English Dictionary&#44; neatly bound&#45;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">In return I shall be very happy&#44; in case I can be of use<lb/> to you&#44; to offer you my services&#44; and remain&#44; Dear Sir&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(11)">Yours very truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">A Myerston</persName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><addressee>Isaac Leeser Esqr</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>371 Walnut <sic>street</sic></placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi></placeName></p>
          
        </body>
